From https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/cs/degree-reqs/enrollment-policy#lower:

"As soon as all undergraduate students have had their Phase II appointment, no seats will continue to be held for students with particular majors. Similarly, juniors and senior L&S students will also be able to be admitted to these classes at this time. Since now the waitlist will be processed in order, students with other majors and L&S juniors and seniors who used Phase I and Phase II to prioritize these classes will be enrolled before EECS and undeclared L&S students who wait until open enrollment to sign up for these classes."

From this you can infer that if you are on the waitlist you will be processed behind everyone who is ahead of you regardless of major status.

Hello , I am a second year EECS student and I had a time conflict with CS 70. I submitted a SIS time conflict request but they just got back to me and said I had entered the numbers wrong. I resubmitted the form and also filled out the one posted here just in case. However now CS 70 is full, my question is that if I get on to the waitlist, will I have priority over non-majors in getting off the waitlist or will I have to wait with everybody else.
